<subSubSection id="14B8651DCA57FFF1D7F1FC7EFEE8FA4B" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5C1D3696CA57FFF1D7F1FC7EFEE8FA4B" blockId="18.[151,1437,945,1475]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D7F1FC7EFE8EFC43" bold="true" box="[151,267,945,971]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Remarks.</emphasis>
The four species here included in the 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D5A8FC7EFCB5FC43" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[718,816,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerna">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D5A8FC7EFCB5FC43" box="[718,816,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">A. cerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group were only recently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="38334B67CA57FFF1D261FC7EFF67FC67" author="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr." firstAuthor="Olah" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="131 - 213" part="104" refId="ref15616" refString="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr. (2012) Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 104, 131 - 213." title="Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Oláh &amp; Flint (2012)</bibRefCitation>
and they are very similar in the general aspect of male genitalia. This species group is defined by the adult male having the following characteristics: (1) segment VII with a long ventromesal process; (2) the posterior margin of segment VIII has a deep U-shaped or V-shaped incision in ventral view; (3) segment IX has a pair of long dorsolateral processes, each ending in one or more robust spines; and (4) the inferior appendages are fused to each other only in their basal area and (5) each has a long rod-like lateral process. In some morphological features, e.g. the inferior appendages with lateral processes, the conspicuous subgenital plate, the internal spines in the phallus, this group resembles species of 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D6B5FB62FDD8FB4F" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1937" box="[467,605,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Zumatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D6B5FB62FDD8FB4F" box="[467,605,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Zumatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the phylogenetic hypotheses from Bayesian Inference presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="38334B67CA57FFF1D7DAFB1EFE1AFB64" author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[188,415,1233,1260]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D676FB1DFEC1FB63" box="[272,324,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
indicate this, with “ 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D5E1FB1EFCBFFB63" box="[647,826,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leucotrichiinae">Leucotrichiinae</taxonomicName>
genus B” (= 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D4BEFB1EFA10FB63" authority="Olah &amp; Flint 2012" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[984,1429,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ujasa">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D4BEFB1EFB30FB63" box="[984,1205,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Acostatrichia ujasa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="38334B67CA57FFF1D3D8FB1EFA10FB63" author="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[1214,1429,1233,1259]" firstAuthor="Olah" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="131 - 213" part="104" refId="ref15616" refString="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr. (2012) Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 104, 131 - 213." title="Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Oláh &amp; Flint 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) as sister group to the 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D6ECFB3AFD91FA87" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1937" box="[394,532,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Zumatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D6ECFB3AFD91FA87" box="[394,532,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Zumatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. However, this species (and others in the group) lacks the synapomorphic features of 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D67EFAD6FE27FABB" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1937" box="[280,418,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Zumatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D67EFAD6FE27FABB" box="[280,418,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Zumatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the modified scape and the presence of preanal processes (
<bibRefCitation id="38334B67CA57FFF1D30FFAD6FAB9FABC" author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[1129,1340,1305,1332]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D3D8FAD5FB75FABB" box="[1214,1264,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, the results of parsimony analyses presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="38334B67CA57FFF1D459FAF2FBA5FAD0" author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[831,1056,1341,1368]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D4F5FAF1FC43FADF" box="[915,966,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
show “ 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D311FAF2FAAFFADF" box="[1143,1322,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leucotrichiinae">Leucotrichiinae</taxonomicName>
genus B” closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D639FAAEFE73FAF3" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[351,502,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D639FAAEFE73FAF3" box="[351,502,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Acostatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. Because of the uncertainty about their phylogenetic affinities, the original assignment to 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D65CFA4AFE54FA17" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[314,465,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D65CFA4AFE54FA17" box="[314,465,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Acostatrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is followed here, but the 
<taxonomicName id="9BA24D15CA57FFF1D596FA4AFCCAFA17" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[752,847,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerna">
<emphasis id="6ED6EA84CA57FFF1D596FA4AFCCAFA17" box="[752,847,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">A. cerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group probably constitutes a distinct lineage within the leucotrichiines.
</paragraph>
